http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: A figure of speech is a word or phrase that possesses a separate meaning from its literal definition
A line is a subdivision of a poem, specifically a group of words arranged into a row that ends for a reason other than the right-hand margin.
Literary movements are a way to divide literature into categories of similar philosophical, topical, or aesthetic features, as opposed to divisions by genre or period.
A human being regarded as an individual.
A piece of writing in which the expression of feelings and ideas is given intensity by particular attention to diction (sometimes involving rhyme), rhythm, and imagery.
One (such as a creative artist) of great imaginative and expressive capabilities and special sensitivity to the medium that writes poems
An idea, concept or topic that recurs in or pervades a work of art or literature.
